    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1867-10-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1867-10-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="333" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d333">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Plumb</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Seward</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 19.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">City of Mexico,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1867-10-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 18, 1867</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Referring to your despatch No. 16, of the
                            15th August last, addressed to Mr. Otterbourg, I have the honor to
                            state, that in an interview with Mr. Lerdo de Tejada on the 13th
                            instant, I took occasion to read to him that portion <pb facs="0533" n="463" xml:id="pg_463"/> of said despatch which you directed should
                            be communicated to the minister of foreign relations.</p>
                <p>Mr. Lerdo de Tejada in reply expressed himself to the effect that any
                            action on the part of the government of the United States could only
                            receive consideration at the hands of the government of Mexico.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, very respectfully, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>E. L. PLUMB.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William H. Seward,</hi>
                        <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State, Washington, D. C.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
